# Backup Exception – Legal Hold (Cohesity)

## 1. Overview
This document defines the Legal Hold control within backup data protection platforms.  
The purpose is to preserve selected backup snapshots for legal, regulatory, or investigation requirements by preventing deletion or expiry.

Applies to workloads protected in Cohesity including databases, virtual machines, and file systems.

---

## 2. Accepted Security Policy (Conforming Use)
Legal Hold is an approved exception to standard retention policies and is permitted only when:

- A valid Legal/Compliance request is received  
- Specific snapshots must be preserved beyond retention  
- Data preservation is required for audit, investigation, or regulatory purposes  

---

## 3. Exception Guidelines (Legal Hold)
Legal Hold is applied only to identified snapshots that require preservation.

| Control Type | Description |
|---|---|
| Snapshot Preservation | Prevents deletion and expiry of selected snapshots |
| Retention Override | Overrides configured retention policies |
| Scoped Application | Applied only to required objects/snapshots |

---

## 4. Impact Guidelines

| Backup Object | Example | Impact | Reason |
|---|---|---|---|
| Database Systems | DB backups under hold | Medium | Retained longer than required |
| Virtual Machines | VM snapshots under hold | Medium | Increased storage usage |
| File Storage | NAS/File snapshots | Medium | Retention override |
| Storage Capacity | All held snapshots | High | Storage growth due to no expiry |

---

## 5. Exception Handling – Legal Hold (Cohesity)

### Purpose
To ensure preservation of backup data for legal, regulatory, or investigation requirements.

### Control Statement
Cohesity Legal Hold is applied at the snapshot level to override retention policies and prevent deletion until formally released.

### Implementation

| Area | Details |
|---|---|
| Platform | Cohesity |
| Level | Snapshot-level |
| Configuration | Applied via UI/API |
| Scope | VMs, databases, files |
| Dependency | Valid snapshot availability |

### Process
1. Legal/Compliance request received  
2. Snapshots identified  
3. Legal Hold applied  
4. Protection verified  
5. Periodic review  
6. Release upon approval  

### Exception Handling
- Overrides retention policies  
- Excluded from cleanup/expiry jobs  

### Audit & Evidence
- Screenshots of Legal Hold  
- Snapshot/object list  
- Approval records (JIRA/Email)  
- Verification of non-expiry  

---

## 6. Appendix
Refer Cohesity documentation:  
https://docs.cohesity.com/baas/data-protect/LegalHoldSnapshot.htm  

---

## 7. Definitions

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| Legal Hold | Preservation of snapshots beyond retention |
| Snapshot | Point-in-time backup copy |
| Retention Override | Bypassing standard retention policy |
| Recovery Capability | Ability to restore data |

